WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.559
And aren't you thankful for the love of God?

00:00:02.559 --> 00:00:04.760
And we've been singing about it all morning.

00:00:04.760 --> 00:00:06.800
And 1 John chapter number three,

00:00:06.800 --> 00:00:10.359
I know that our series is through the book of James,

00:00:10.359 --> 00:00:13.439
our theme this year, doers of the word.

00:00:13.439 --> 00:00:16.079
But the Lord really impressed upon my heart this week

00:00:16.079 --> 00:00:18.840
to preach from 1 John chapter number three,

00:00:18.840 --> 00:00:21.319
and looking forward to looking at this portion

00:00:21.319 --> 00:00:22.760
of scripture this morning,

00:00:22.760 --> 00:00:24.840
and really thinking about the love of God.

00:00:24.840 --> 00:00:27.479
I titled the message, Jesus loves even me.

00:00:27.520 --> 00:00:28.920
And I know we sang that song

00:00:28.920 --> 00:00:31.159
to begin the service this morning.

00:00:31.159 --> 00:00:35.439
And I'm so thankful, wonderful things in the Bible I see,

00:00:35.439 --> 00:00:39.200
but this is the dearest that Jesus loves me.

00:00:39.200 --> 00:00:40.720
And what a blessing.

00:00:40.720 --> 00:00:43.159
And some of you know, and you've experienced the fact,

00:00:43.159 --> 00:00:45.119
yesterday, of course, was Valentine's day.

00:00:45.119 --> 00:00:48.200
And it seems like even before Christmas was over,

00:00:48.200 --> 00:00:49.560
if you were in any of the stores,

00:00:49.560 --> 00:00:51.799
you already saw things that were out

00:00:51.799 --> 00:00:53.180
for Valentine's day, right?

00:00:53.180 --> 00:00:55.560
The candy, the decorations, all those kinds of things.

00:00:55.560 --> 00:00:57.639
And if you went this past week

00:00:57.639 --> 00:00:59.479
to find some things for Valentine's day,

00:00:59.479 --> 00:01:00.680
you found that there were a bunch of things

00:01:00.680 --> 00:01:02.240
for Easter out already.

00:01:02.240 --> 00:01:04.720
And it seems like before one holiday passes,

00:01:04.720 --> 00:01:07.080
they already have all of the merchandise

00:01:07.080 --> 00:01:08.800
for the next holiday ready for you,

00:01:08.800 --> 00:01:12.080
because we're a consumer driven society.

00:01:12.080 --> 00:01:15.080
In fact, I did a little research this past week.

00:01:15.080 --> 00:01:18.360
And in that research, I discovered

00:01:18.360 --> 00:01:22.120
that it was projected in the US economy

00:01:22.120 --> 00:01:24.800
that yesterday, Valentine's day,

00:01:24.800 --> 00:01:26.879
that it was expected, projected,

00:01:26.879 --> 00:01:31.680
that it would be $29.1 billion spent

00:01:31.680 --> 00:01:36.680
on Valentine's day, $29.1 billion.

00:01:36.720 --> 00:01:37.919
That's a lot of money.

00:01:37.919 --> 00:01:42.040
And the reality is that if you bought a card,

00:01:42.040 --> 00:01:45.199
you bought candy, you bought flowers, jewelry,

00:01:45.199 --> 00:01:47.319
took your sweet one out to dinner,

00:01:47.319 --> 00:01:51.279
then yes, you participated in that $29.1 billion.

00:01:52.199 --> 00:01:54.760
And many of us, especially all the men,

00:01:54.760 --> 00:01:56.000
you ought to be able to raise your hand and say,

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.720
I participated in that $29.1 billion, amen?

00:02:00.720 --> 00:02:02.720
And praise the Lord.

00:02:02.720 --> 00:02:04.319
And really, when we think about that,

00:02:04.319 --> 00:02:07.000
and we think about all that takes place

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:09.360
in our society with that,

00:02:09.360 --> 00:02:11.639
really, what I'd boil it all down to

00:02:11.639 --> 00:02:15.960
is that it's an attempt by an individual

00:02:15.960 --> 00:02:19.300
to do one thing, and that's to express their love,

00:02:19.300 --> 00:02:20.800
to express their love.

00:02:21.320 --> 00:02:24.279
Holly told me years ago, and at the beginning,

00:02:24.279 --> 00:02:25.720
and any of those that have been married,

00:02:25.720 --> 00:02:27.800
we're gonna celebrate 25 years this year,

00:02:27.800 --> 00:02:30.240
any of those that have been married for far less than that,

00:02:30.240 --> 00:02:32.220
you might wanna check it out for a couple of years

00:02:32.220 --> 00:02:34.800
to make sure it's correct, but early on,

00:02:34.800 --> 00:02:37.080
Holly said, please do not buy me flowers

00:02:37.080 --> 00:02:39.779
at Valentine's day, because they just double

00:02:39.779 --> 00:02:42.600
or triple in price, and so please don't do that.

00:02:42.600 --> 00:02:44.520
And the first year, I kinda thought,

00:02:44.520 --> 00:02:47.720
is she being honest, like, is this a setup?

00:02:47.720 --> 00:02:49.800
Like, I buy them, and I don't,

00:02:49.919 --> 00:02:51.960
honey, you said don't buy them, whatever,

00:02:51.960 --> 00:02:54.559
but now I know she's being very real with me.

00:02:54.559 --> 00:02:56.919
I don't want you to buy flowers at Valentine's day,

00:02:56.919 --> 00:02:58.080
and so I haven't bought flowers

00:02:58.080 --> 00:03:00.279
on Valentine's day for a long time,

00:03:00.279 --> 00:03:02.679
but I'll buy flowers other times of the year, right?

00:03:02.679 --> 00:03:04.919
Just kinda surprise her with flowers,

00:03:04.919 --> 00:03:06.880
and that's always a good thing,

00:03:06.880 --> 00:03:09.460
but really, it's an attempt to express love,

00:03:09.460 --> 00:03:11.559
and as I was considering the reality

00:03:11.559 --> 00:03:15.360
and kinda finding myself kinda anywhere you go

00:03:15.360 --> 00:03:17.399
over the last several weeks, you go into the store,

00:03:17.399 --> 00:03:19.759
and you see all of this right in front of you, right?

00:03:20.600 --> 00:03:21.440
You gotta buy a card, you gotta buy this,

00:03:21.440 --> 00:03:23.039
and all these things that are going on,

00:03:23.039 --> 00:03:25.440
and it caused me, as I was thinking about that,

00:03:25.440 --> 00:03:28.520
to just be reminded of God's love.

00:03:29.580 --> 00:03:32.479
And I'm so thankful that we have a Bible

00:03:32.479 --> 00:03:34.919
that, as we read the scriptures,

00:03:34.919 --> 00:03:38.320
we consider some very precious verses

00:03:38.320 --> 00:03:40.679
that God gives us in his word

00:03:40.679 --> 00:03:43.399
that teach us of God's love.

00:03:43.399 --> 00:03:46.699
Not only do we have a Bible that's given to us

00:03:46.699 --> 00:03:50.220
by inspiration, providentially preserved for us,

00:03:50.220 --> 00:03:54.580
and we can trust what God has given to us in his word,

00:03:54.580 --> 00:03:57.020
but we have many that have written songs

00:03:57.020 --> 00:03:58.940
about the love of God,

00:03:58.940 --> 00:04:01.339
and one of the first songs that many of us

00:04:01.339 --> 00:04:03.899
may remember singing in Sunday school

00:04:03.899 --> 00:04:05.259
if we grew up in church,

00:04:05.259 --> 00:04:07.539
one of the songs that maybe we remember teaching

00:04:07.539 --> 00:04:11.220
our children, a Sunday school song,

00:04:11.220 --> 00:04:14.460
Jesus loves me, this I know,

00:04:14.460 --> 00:04:16.859
for the Bible tells me so.

00:04:16.859 --> 00:04:18.100
Isn't it wonderful?

00:04:18.100 --> 00:04:20.739
I mean, just a sweet little Sunday school song,

00:04:20.739 --> 00:04:23.940
but man, the power, the truth,

00:04:23.940 --> 00:04:26.579
that is contained in that little song,

00:04:26.579 --> 00:04:29.420
and oftentimes, as I would teach children

00:04:29.420 --> 00:04:31.299
in Sunday school, in children's church,

00:04:31.299 --> 00:04:33.299
I would, vacation Bible schools,

00:04:33.299 --> 00:04:35.200
I would say, now tell me a verse of scripture

00:04:35.200 --> 00:04:37.820
that tells us that God loves us,

00:04:37.820 --> 00:04:40.899
because the song says, Jesus loves me, this I know,

00:04:40.899 --> 00:04:43.619
for the Bible tells me so,

00:04:43.700 --> 00:04:45.700
and God's word is trustworthy,

00:04:45.700 --> 00:04:49.459
it is dependable, and we find that God's word

00:04:49.459 --> 00:04:53.579
is full of truth with regard to the subject of love,

00:04:53.579 --> 00:04:56.540
and I'm thankful to be a personal recipient

00:04:56.540 --> 00:05:00.980
of God's love, Jesus loves even me.

00:05:00.980 --> 00:05:04.980
Look at the text of scripture before us in 1 John 3.

00:05:04.980 --> 00:05:07.019
I'm gonna read the first three verses,

00:05:07.019 --> 00:05:08.700
and then make some comments here

00:05:08.700 --> 00:05:11.820
as we look at a number of verses of scripture this morning,

00:05:11.820 --> 00:05:14.739
but I want you to notice what the Apostle John says

00:05:14.739 --> 00:05:15.579
as he's writing here,

00:05:15.579 --> 00:05:17.739
under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit of God,

00:05:17.739 --> 00:05:19.380
the Bible says this in verse number one,

00:05:19.380 --> 00:05:24.380
behold, behold what manner of love

00:05:24.940 --> 00:05:29.160
the Father hath bestowed upon us,

00:05:29.160 --> 00:05:33.220
that we should be called the sons of God,

00:05:33.220 --> 00:05:35.600
therefore the world knoweth us not,

00:05:35.600 --> 00:05:38.459
because it knew him not.

00:05:38.459 --> 00:05:43.260
Beloved, now are we the sons of God,

00:05:43.260 --> 00:05:46.619
and it doth not yet appear what we shall be,

00:05:46.619 --> 00:05:50.059
but we know that when he shall appear,

00:05:50.059 --> 00:05:55.059
we shall be like him, for we shall see him as he is,

00:05:57.619 --> 00:06:00.899
and every man that hath this hope in him,

00:06:00.899 --> 00:06:05.899
purifieth himself even as he is pure,

00:06:06.059 --> 00:06:08.899
isn't that a precious portion of God's word?

00:06:08.899 --> 00:06:10.980
We find that as we look at this text,

00:06:10.980 --> 00:06:12.459
if you're taking notes this morning,

00:06:12.459 --> 00:06:14.100
let me share with you number one,

00:06:14.100 --> 00:06:15.980
the recognition of John,

00:06:15.980 --> 00:06:18.619
John recognizes something that's so important

00:06:18.619 --> 00:06:21.220
for every individual to recognize,

00:06:21.220 --> 00:06:22.619
in fact, this morning,

00:06:22.619 --> 00:06:24.619
there are some here that are gathered

00:06:24.619 --> 00:06:27.619
that you've already recognized this truth,

00:06:27.619 --> 00:06:31.619
and yet perhaps there's some others that are gathered here,

00:06:31.619 --> 00:06:34.779
maybe some that are tuned in via live stream this morning

00:06:34.779 --> 00:06:39.420
that have never recognized what John recognizes here,

00:06:39.420 --> 00:06:42.019
and records for us in verse number one,

00:06:42.019 --> 00:06:43.179
when he says this,

00:06:43.179 --> 00:06:44.660
behold, notice what he says,

00:06:44.660 --> 00:06:49.660
what manner of love the Father hath bestowed upon us.

00:06:51.540 --> 00:06:55.700
That word manner gives the idea of what sort,

00:06:55.700 --> 00:06:57.779
the subject here being love,

00:06:57.779 --> 00:07:00.899
what sort of love, the quality of the love,

00:07:00.899 --> 00:07:03.299
we're familiar, and we'll look at some other verses here

00:07:03.299 --> 00:07:05.739
in just a few moments of God expressing

00:07:05.739 --> 00:07:09.700
and declaring his love for his people,

00:07:09.700 --> 00:07:11.739
and we find that the apostle John,

00:07:11.739 --> 00:07:13.899
as he's recognizing this truth,

00:07:13.899 --> 00:07:17.140
he says, behold, what manner of love the Father,

00:07:17.140 --> 00:07:18.339
notice what he says,

00:07:18.339 --> 00:07:21.500
hath bestowed upon us.

00:07:21.500 --> 00:07:24.179
Now, John is using himself here

00:07:24.179 --> 00:07:27.459
as one of those that is the recipient of God's love,

00:07:27.459 --> 00:07:29.980
he's writing to these that have been saved

00:07:29.980 --> 00:07:31.019
by the grace of God,

00:07:31.019 --> 00:07:34.140
and he's giving instruction in the book of 1 John,

00:07:34.140 --> 00:07:35.500
and those that have been saved,

00:07:35.500 --> 00:07:37.540
he says, listen, I wanna remind you,

00:07:37.540 --> 00:07:39.299
I want us to recognize,

00:07:39.299 --> 00:07:41.779
never get over the wonderful truth

00:07:41.779 --> 00:07:46.779
of what manner of love the Father hath bestowed upon us.

00:07:47.540 --> 00:07:51.859
I'm so thankful that this portion of scripture

00:07:51.859 --> 00:07:52.820
is given to us,

00:07:52.820 --> 00:07:56.100
and that John recognized the truth

00:07:56.100 --> 00:07:59.339
that God loved him personally.

00:07:59.339 --> 00:08:00.980
We often talk about the truth

00:08:00.980 --> 00:08:03.799
that God is a global God,

00:08:03.799 --> 00:08:04.640
and he is,

00:08:04.640 --> 00:08:05.980
and God so loved the world,

00:08:05.980 --> 00:08:07.779
and we'll look at that in just a moment,

00:08:07.779 --> 00:08:10.739
but we find that we rejoice greatly

00:08:10.739 --> 00:08:12.500
in knowing that personally,

00:08:12.500 --> 00:08:14.299
God loves me,

00:08:14.299 --> 00:08:15.859
and personally, this morning,

00:08:15.859 --> 00:08:18.579
God loves you.

00:08:18.579 --> 00:08:19.779
There was a time in my life

00:08:19.779 --> 00:08:20.859
when I didn't know that,

00:08:20.859 --> 00:08:22.859
I didn't understand that.

00:08:22.859 --> 00:08:25.380
I remember living for years

00:08:25.380 --> 00:08:27.100
and never going to church,

00:08:27.100 --> 00:08:29.179
and never sitting in a Sunday school class,

00:08:30.019 --> 00:08:31.019
and never singing that song,

00:08:31.019 --> 00:08:32.940
Jesus loves me, this I know.

00:08:32.940 --> 00:08:33.780
Why?

00:08:33.780 --> 00:08:34.760
Because I didn't grow up in church,

00:08:34.760 --> 00:08:36.179
and I wasn't there.

00:08:36.179 --> 00:08:37.859
Some of these young people in our church,

00:08:37.859 --> 00:08:40.539
they've known that song seemingly forever,

00:08:40.539 --> 00:08:42.140
but I, as a 17 year,

00:08:42.140 --> 00:08:43.219
well, probably earlier than that,

00:08:43.219 --> 00:08:44.380
because I didn't get saved until I was 17,

00:08:44.380 --> 00:08:46.119
but when I started going to church,

00:08:46.119 --> 00:08:47.739
I remember hearing that song

00:08:47.739 --> 00:08:49.780
and not fully understanding it,

00:08:49.780 --> 00:08:52.859
and understanding and comprehending what that meant,

00:08:52.859 --> 00:08:54.440
and if someone were to ask me,

00:08:54.440 --> 00:08:55.820
where does the Bible tell you?

00:08:55.820 --> 00:08:57.659
I'd have no answer.

00:08:59.900 --> 00:09:03.500
Perhaps you can remember that time in your life as well.

00:09:03.500 --> 00:09:04.739
Perhaps you can remember

00:09:04.739 --> 00:09:08.419
when you were not aware of God's love for you.

00:09:08.419 --> 00:09:09.940
There was a time in your life

00:09:09.940 --> 00:09:11.539
where you were lost,

00:09:11.539 --> 00:09:13.059
and you were separated from God,

00:09:13.059 --> 00:09:16.059
and you had no idea that God loved you.

00:09:16.059 --> 00:09:18.500
You had no idea that the God of the universe,

00:09:18.500 --> 00:09:20.359
the one who created you,

00:09:20.359 --> 00:09:21.960
the one who created all things,

00:09:21.960 --> 00:09:25.479
that he loved you personally.

00:09:26.539 --> 00:09:27.580
I remember that.

00:09:28.419 --> 00:09:29.739
Not knowing,

00:09:29.739 --> 00:09:32.979
and then I remember receiving the truth

00:09:32.979 --> 00:09:34.460
that God loved me.

00:09:35.500 --> 00:09:37.940
I remember somebody saying it to me this way,

00:09:37.940 --> 00:09:40.780
that God loved you so much

00:09:40.780 --> 00:09:43.659
that if you were the only person on planet Earth,

00:09:43.659 --> 00:09:46.260
he still would have died for you.

00:09:46.260 --> 00:09:47.099
Wow.

00:09:48.580 --> 00:09:49.580
John here says,

00:09:49.580 --> 00:09:53.859
behold, what manner of love

00:09:53.859 --> 00:09:57.179
the Father hath bestowed upon us.

00:09:57.260 --> 00:09:59.780
We'll look at the rest of the text in just a moment.

00:09:59.780 --> 00:10:00.979
I want you to understand.

00:10:00.979 --> 00:10:03.379
as you read the Bible, it's very interesting

00:10:03.379 --> 00:10:05.079
and we can't look at all the verses.

00:10:05.079 --> 00:10:07.259
We may not even look at all of the verses

00:10:07.259 --> 00:10:09.099
that I have noted here this morning,

00:10:09.099 --> 00:10:11.179
but I want you to understand that as you begin reading

00:10:11.179 --> 00:10:13.779
the Old Testament and you begin reading there

00:10:13.779 --> 00:10:16.259
about God's love, you'll notice some things

00:10:16.259 --> 00:10:17.899
about God's love in the Old Testament.

00:10:17.899 --> 00:10:21.419
You'll notice that it talks about God loving the fathers,

00:10:21.419 --> 00:10:26.419
meaning the heads of Israel, the forefathers,

00:10:26.459 --> 00:10:29.959
if you will, of Israel, Abraham and Isaac and Jacob

00:10:29.999 --> 00:10:31.039
and so on and so forth.

00:10:31.039 --> 00:10:33.559
You'll read of God loving the nation.

00:10:33.559 --> 00:10:37.019
You'll read of God's love for Israel.

00:10:37.019 --> 00:10:39.479
In fact, look, if you will, at a few verses

00:10:39.479 --> 00:10:42.159
in the book of Deuteronomy and we'll notice

00:10:42.159 --> 00:10:44.159
how the scriptures reveal this to us

00:10:44.159 --> 00:10:45.799
as you read the Old Testament.

00:10:45.799 --> 00:10:48.279
And we find that in Deuteronomy chapter number four,

00:10:48.279 --> 00:10:50.739
we'll just look at a few verses right here in Deuteronomy.

00:10:50.739 --> 00:10:55.039
And I want you to see that as we progress through this

00:10:55.039 --> 00:10:58.279
this morning and we come to where we are with John

00:10:58.319 --> 00:11:01.479
and first John and we understand his love for me

00:11:01.479 --> 00:11:04.679
as an individual, his love for me personally,

00:11:04.679 --> 00:11:08.399
how impactful that truth is.

00:11:08.399 --> 00:11:09.939
In Deuteronomy chapter number four,

00:11:09.939 --> 00:11:11.399
look at verse number 37.

00:11:11.399 --> 00:11:14.599
The Bible says this in Deuteronomy four and verse 37,

00:11:14.599 --> 00:11:17.959
and because he loved thy fathers,

00:11:17.959 --> 00:11:21.079
therefore he chose their seed after them

00:11:21.079 --> 00:11:23.399
and brought thee out in his sight

00:11:23.399 --> 00:11:26.359
with his mighty power out of Egypt.

00:11:26.359 --> 00:11:27.899
Turn over to chapter seven, if you will,

00:11:28.519 --> 00:11:31.039
here in the book of Deuteronomy chapter seven.

00:11:31.039 --> 00:11:34.179
In verse number seven, the Bible says this,

00:11:34.179 --> 00:11:39.179
the Lord did not set his love upon you nor choose you

00:11:39.479 --> 00:11:41.959
because you were more in number than any people

00:11:41.959 --> 00:11:44.799
for you were the fewest of all people.

00:11:44.799 --> 00:11:47.199
But because the Lord loved you

00:11:47.199 --> 00:11:49.319
and because he would keep the oath

00:11:49.319 --> 00:11:51.519
which he had sworn unto your fathers,

00:11:51.519 --> 00:11:54.439
hath the Lord brought you out with a mighty hand

00:11:54.439 --> 00:11:57.439
and redeemed you out of the house of bondmen

00:11:57.439 --> 00:12:00.579
from the hand of Pharaoh, king of Egypt.

00:12:00.579 --> 00:12:04.179
Look at chapter 10, if you will, in Deuteronomy chapter 10.

00:12:04.179 --> 00:12:06.499
And look, notice in verse number 15,

00:12:06.499 --> 00:12:10.299
and again, Moses here is reminding the people

00:12:10.299 --> 00:12:11.739
as they would prepare for entering

00:12:11.739 --> 00:12:13.339
into the land of promise.

00:12:13.339 --> 00:12:15.539
And he's reminding them here in these verses

00:12:15.539 --> 00:12:17.739
that I've selected about God's love

00:12:17.739 --> 00:12:19.499
in verse 15 of Deuteronomy 10,

00:12:19.499 --> 00:12:21.499
the Bible says only the Lord had a delight

00:12:21.499 --> 00:12:23.859
in thy fathers to love them

00:12:23.859 --> 00:12:25.979
and he chose their seed after them,

